
#' Spatial and Household elements of Epidemic

# ==== Simple ====
Start with NxM grid with each unit of grid pertaining to one person

Subjects in units which are closer to a given subject have a stronger force of infection, and are therefore more likely to pass infection (if infectious).

# ==== Household ====

Each Unit holds a household which contains h subjects

Force of infection between subjects which reside in the same household is significantly higher

Same spatially varying force of infection

# ==== Social Network ====

Schools, Places of work, Hospitals

Agent-based modelling?






